title> a hunt</span><hr size=1> &quot;My dear, Sin,&quot; she smiled darkly upon the familiar.  &quot;a hunt for you.  But, this prey I want brought back alive. She is Maia, the Pleiade.  A daughter of Atlas and now mother to the new Olympian, Hermes.  I want her here...unharmed if possible.  And I shall think of how or what I will do to the harlot.&quot; Hera almost hissed as she spoke.  This was a game she was well used to.  Tormenting those who decided to sleep with her husband.  Of course, it was not the first time for Maia. So, this time....Hera would make sure was the last time, that Maia thought to bed Zeus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ulionessofhera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lioness of Hera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/1/01 5:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> a hunt</span><hr size=1> As Hera spoke of the hunt, Sin smiled.  Her huntress heart raced at the thought of the chase and the scent of fear. <br>
